strmprivacy.api.entities.v1.BatchJob.description:
********************************
Batch Jobs
Currently we only support:
- CSV as DataFormat type
- a clean database for every batch job
- CSV files with a header row, because the header is needed to get the field names
*******************************

id.title: string id = 2;
id.description: the UUIDv4 of the job, generated upon creation

project_id.title: string project_id = 3;
project_id.description: the UUIDv4 of the STRM Privacy project

name.title: string name = 2;
name.description: constraints: generic name constraint, unique within handle

strmprivacy.api.entities.v1.ConsentLevel.description:
Consent level is meant to interpret the consent-levels of an event for decryption purposes only.

Cumulative means that the highest consent-level in an event must be greater than or equal to the single requested level
for the decrypted stream.

Granular means that the set of consent-levels in an event must enclose the set of requested event levels for the
decrypted stream.

file_name.title: string file_name = 3;
file_name.description:
(-- api-linter: core::0122::name-suffix=disabled
     aip.dev/not-precedent: We think file_name is a better name. --)

path_prefix.title: string path_prefix = 2;
path_prefix.description: If omitted, files are read from the root of the bucket.

field_patterns.title: map<string, strmprivacy.api.entities.v1.MaskedFields.PatternList> field_patterns = 3;
field_patterns.description:
map of event-contract-ref vs field patterns

constraints:
 data-contract-refs should be existing data contracts
 field_patterns should be valid values (checked by events-core)
 the field_patterns list should have no duplicates.

id.title: string id = 1;
id.description: IANA Time Zone Database time zone, e.g. "America/New_York".

version.title: string version = 2;
version.description: Optional. IANA Time Zone Database version number, e.g. "2019a".
